Acoustic Wireless Power Transfer: A Comprehensive Technical Whitepaper

Document: AWE-TWP-2024-001
Version: 1.0
Date: November 5, 2024
Authors: Advanced Wireless Energy Research Consortium
Confidentiality: Public Distribution

---

Abstract

This whitepaper presents a comprehensive technical analysis of Ultrasonic Energy Transfer (UET) systems for wireless power transmission through atmospheric and liquid media. We detail the physics, engineering implementation, performance characteristics, and emerging applications of this transformative technology. Unlike electromagnetic wireless power solutions, UET operates on mechanical pressure waves, offering unique advantages in environments where electromagnetic interference, safety concerns, or medium opacity present challenges. This document provides system architects, engineers, and decision-makers with the technical foundation to evaluate, design, and deploy UET systems across medical, industrial, consumer, and aerospace domains.

