12. Appendices

Appendix A: Mathematical Derivations

A.1 Piezoelectric Constitutive Equations
The linear piezoelectric constitutive relations:

\begin{bmatrix}
S \\
D
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
s^E & d^t \\
d & \epsilon^T
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
T \\
E
\end{bmatrix}

Where the superscript t indicates transpose.

A.2 Acoustic Radiation Impedance
For a baffled circular piston of radius a:

Z_r = \rho_0 c \pi a^2 \left[ 1 - \frac{J_1(2ka)}{ka} + j \frac{H_1(2ka)}{ka} \right]

Where J_1 is the Bessel function of first kind and H_1 is the Struve function.

Appendix B: Test Methodologies

B.1 Efficiency Measurement Protocol

1. Electrical input power measurement at transmitter DC input
2. Acoustic power measurement using radiation force balance or calorimetric method
3. Electrical output power measurement at receiver DC output
4. System efficiency calculation: \eta = \frac{P_{out}}{P_{in}} \times 100\%

B.2 Beam Pattern Characterization

· Use automated XY scanner with calibrated hydrophone
· Spatial sampling: ≤λ/2 at highest frequency
· Far-field measurements: Distance > 2D^2/\lambda where D is array diameter
· Data analysis: Beam width, side lobe levels, directivity index

Appendix C: Design Guidelines

C.1 Transducer Array Design Checklist

· Element spacing ≤ λ/2 at maximum frequency to avoid grating lobes
· Matching layer impedance Z_m = \sqrt{Z_p Z_{medium}}
· Matching layer thickness = λ/4 at center frequency
· Backing material impedance matched to piezoelectric for bandwidth
· Thermal management for continuous operation

C.2 System Integration Checklist

· Safety interlocks implemented and tested
· EMI/EMC pre-compliance testing completed
· Environmental testing (temperature, humidity, vibration)
· User documentation and training materials
· Service and maintenance procedures defined

